"title": "8474: seeing God",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "8474: seeing god",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Perceiving God in all his fulness. Scripture stresses that God, as spirit, is invisible to sinful human beings. He has, however, been revealed in Jesus Christ, who is his perfect likeness, and he will be seen in all his glory at the end of history when he comes in judgment.</p>\n<h2>No human can see the face of God in all his fulness</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim6:15-1Tim6:16\">1TI 6:15–6:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut4:10-Deut4:12\">DEU 4:10–4:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John6:46\">JHN 6:46</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim1:17\">1TI 1:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John4:12\">1JN 4:12</a></p>\n<h2>Privileged individuals may catch a glimpse of God</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod33:21-Exod33:23\">EXO 33:21–33:23</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen16:13-Gen16:14\">GEN 16:13–16:14</a> <em>Hagar</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num12:5-Num12:8\">NUM 12:5–12:8</a> <em>Moses</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg6:11-Judg6:24\">JDG 6:11–6:24</a> <em>Gideon</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg13:2-Judg13:23\">JDG 13:2–13:23</a> <em>Manoah and his wife</em></p>\n<h2>Threat of death on seeing the face of God</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod33:20\">EXO 33:20</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen32:24-Gen32:30\">GEN 32:24–32:30</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod19:21\">EXO 19:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod24:9-Exod24:11\">EXO 24:9–24:11</a></p>\n<h2>Seeing God in a vision</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa6:1\">ISA 6:1</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs22:19\">1KI 22:19</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr18:18\">2CH 18:18</a> <em>Micaiah</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek1:1-Ezek1:28\">EZK 1:1–1:28</a> <em>Ezekiel</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts7:55-Acts7:56\">ACT 7:55–7:56</a> <em>Stephen</em></p>\n<h2>God may be seen in Jesus Christ</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John14:8-John14:9\">JHN 14:8–14:9</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col1:15\">COL 1:15</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John1:1-John1:18\">JHN 1:1–1:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John5:20\">1JN 5:20</a></p>\n<h2>The hope of seeing God at the resurrection</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor13:12\">1CO 13:12</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job19:26-Job19:27\">JOB 19:26–19:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps17:15\">PSA 17:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt5:8\">MAT 5:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor13:12\">1CO 13:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb12:14\">HEB 12:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev1:7\">REV 1:7</a></p>",
